http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/Delhi-Police-detain-suspected-militants-in-Uttarakhand/article14008125.ece

Sources claimed that Delhi Police Special Cell has detained four suspected militants. The suspects were held in Uttarakhand in a joint operation conducted by the Cell and other agencies.Sources said that the suspects were there to launch a strike on a religious event in the hilly State. It is learnt that the suspects will be brought to the Capital for further questioning. With the Ardh Kumbh being held in Haridawar, raids are on to nab more suspects.